<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2481] OOM due to message expiry processing with large numbers of messages in queue because of slow or absent consumers.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2481</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when a large of messages in queue,and no consumer or the consumer is very&lt;br/&gt;
slow, the OOM problem occur, because :&lt;br/&gt;
in org.apache.activemq.broker.region.Queue,the 588 line is :&lt;br/&gt;
 doBrowse(true, browsedMessages, this.getMaxExpirePageSize());&lt;br/&gt;
,transform to :&lt;br/&gt;
doBrowse(false, browsedMessages, this.getMaxExpirePageSize());&lt;br/&gt;
 is ok.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;from user list: &lt;a href=&quot;http://old.nabble.com/Out-of-Memory-on-5.3-ts26064098.html#a26264779&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://old.nabble.com/Out-of-Memory-on-5.3-ts26064098.html#a26264779&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Problem is messages get paged into memory with out any limiter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
disabling periodic expiry processing using a destination policy can work around this. set expireMessagesPeriod = 0&lt;/p&gt;</description>
